value.value: Adult ascending neuron with contralateral arbors in the VNC (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a secondary neuron of the 09B hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It exits the VNC via the cervical connective (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Within the VNC it fasciculates with the ventral median tract of ventral cervical fasciculus (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the abdominal neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
